<h2 class="StepsTitle">Steps</h2>
<p id="text">
    1. Mix the sugar, hot water and yeast together in a bowl and leave to sit for 10 minutes 
    <br><br>
    2. Add your flour, salt and baking powder together in a bowl and pour in your yeast mixture.
    <br><br>
    3. place an excess amount of flour onto the surface your working on and begin to kneed the dough for about 5-10 minutes until it reaches soft but non-sticky consistency.
    <br><br>
    4. Grab the baking tray that you're using and line it with baking paper.  Set your oven to 180 degrees celcius. Place some flour and try to spread the dough into a circular shape. This will become your pizza base. When it reaches the radius you want, you can start to add toppings.
    <br><br>
    5. Add your tomato sauce and spread it across the majority of dough except for about a centimeter from the edge. This will be your crust.
    <br><br>
    6. Add every other topping you would like to have to your pizza and place it into the oven for 15 minutes.
    <br><br>
    7. You should now have a delicious pizza ready to eat!
</p>
<br>
